{"title_page": "Thomas Hat", "text_new": "'''Thomas Hat''', of [[Shaftesbury]], [[Dorset]] (died after 1432), was an English Member of Parliament.\n\nHe was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Shaftesbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Shaftesbury]] in November 1414 and 1425. He was [[mayor of Shaftesbury]] 1403\u20134 and 1409\u201310.<ref>https://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/hat-thomas.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hat, Thomas}}\n[[Category:14th-century births]]\n[[Category:15th-century deaths]]\n[[Category:English MPs November 1414]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Shaftesbury]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1425]]\n{{England-pre1707-MP-stub}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Shaftesbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Shaftesbury]] \n| before= [[Thomas Haselmere]]     \n| before2= [[John Pyjon]]\n| with= [[Walter Biere]]\n| years= Nov. 1414\n| after= ?\n| after2= ?\n}}\n{{end box}}\n", "text_old": "'''Thomas Hat''', of [[Shaftesbury]], [[Dorset]] (died after 1432), was an English Member of Parliament.\n\nHe was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Shaftesbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Shaftesbury]] in November 1414 and 1425. He was [[mayor of Shaftesbury]] 1403-4 and 1409\u201310.<ref>https://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/hat-thomas.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hat, Thomas}}\n[[Category:14th-century births]]\n[[Category:15th-century deaths]]\n[[Category:English MPs November 1414]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Shaftesbury]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1425]]\n{{England-pre1707-MP-stub}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Shaftesbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Shaftesbury]] \n| before= [[Thomas Haselmere]]     \n| before2= [[John Pyjon]]\n| with= [[Walter Biere]]\n| years= Nov. 1414\n| after= ?\n|