{"title_page": "Bini the Bunny", "text_new": "{{unreliable sources|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox animal\n| name                    = Bini the Bunny\n| image                   =Bini and his art.jpg\n| image_upright           = \n| caption                 = Bini and some of his paintings.\n| species                 = ''[[Domestic Rabbit]]''\n| breed                   = [[Holland Lop]]\n| gender                  = Male\n| birth_date              = {{Birth date and age|2012|3|21|mf=yes}}\n| occupation              = \n| employer                = \n| role                    = \n| years_active            = 2012\u2013present\n| known                   = [[Internet Celebrity]]\n| tricks                  = Basketball, Painting, Hair Styling\n| awards                  = Guinness World Record\n| title                   = \n| term                    = \n| predecessor             = \n| successor               = \n| owner                   = Shai Lighter\n| residence               = Los Angeles, California U.S. \n| parents                 = Unknown\n| children                = \n| weight                  = 5 lbs\n| height                  = \n| appearance              = \n| namedafter              = \n| website                 = {{url|http://www.facebook.com/Binithebunny}}\n}}\n'''Bini the Bunny''' is a rabbit, known for a series of videos posted on the internet.<ref>{{cite web | title=Bini, basketball's baddest bunny | website=[[Ynet]] | date=December 31, 1999 | url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4485656,00.html | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}</ref> Bini is a 8-year-old male [[Holland Lop]] rabbit, referred to by the media and fans as the only rabbit in the world who can paint,<ref>{{cite web|title=Talented Little Bunny Creates Beautiful Works Of Art, All On His Own!|url=http://www.jumblejoy.com/artist-bunny|website=Jumble Joy|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> play basketball,<ref>{{cite web | last=Schwartz | first=Nick | title=Here's a bunny that can dunk a basketball | publisher=[[CNN]] | date=June 11, 2013 | url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2013/06/heres-a-bunny-that-can-dunk-a-basketball | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Meet Bini, The Basketball-Dunking Bunny|url=http://www.thepostgame.com/blog/animal-house/201306/meet-bini-basketball-dunking-bunny|website=The Post Game|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> and comb and style hair. \nAs of 2017, Bini and his owner, Shai (Asor) Lighter are [[Guinness World Records|Guinness Book of World Record]] holders for the most slam dunks by a rabbit in one minute.  \nBini's most popular video with over 20 million views was created in 2016, titled \"When Your Bunny is Addicted to Arcade Games\".<ref>{{cite web|title=When your bunny is addicted to arcade games...|url=https://www.facebook.com/binithebunny/videos/705862269561334/|website=Facebook.com|publisher=Bini the Bunny}}</ref> Bini's YouTube channel has more than 180,000 subscribers and his Facebook page has over 250,000 fans.\n\n== Background ==\nBini has starred in more than 60 videos where his talents and intelligence are exemplified. He first became recognizable through his 2013 YouTube video \"Funny bunny plays basketball -Bini the bunny\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Funny bunny plays basketball -Bini the bunny|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r7mC6Q-PSAw|website=Youtube|accessdate=10 September 2017}}</ref> In 2016, Bini and his owner Shai moved from Israel to Los Angeles, California.\n\nBini the Bunny's tricks include playing basketball, painting<ref>{{cite web|title=Monday blues? This PAINTING RABBIT will cheer you right up|url=http://www.shemazing.net/tag/bini-the-bunny/|website=Shemazing.net|accessdate=15 February 2017}}</ref> with acrylic paints on canvas, combing and brushing humans' hair, jumping, dancing and spinning on command.  In April 2020, Bini the Bunny learned to play the guitar and shared it in his first ever guitar-playing video, in which he plays Se\u00f1orita by Shawn Mendes and Camila Cabello<ref>{{Citation|title=Rabbit learns to play Guitar|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g9u7gZyJ1DQ|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>.\n\n== Media appearances ==\n\nBini the Bunny and Shai Lighter appeared on [[The Gong Show]] on ABC on July 26, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Gong Show|url=https://abc.go.com/shows/the-gong-show/episode-guide/season-02/6-alyson-hannigan-will-arnett-lil-rel-howery#recap|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref> The Gong Show starring [[Mike Myers]], and featured celebrity judges: Will Arnett, [[Alyson Hannigan]], and Lil Rel Howery\n\nBini was featured on the cover of Guinness World Records: Amazing Animals released in September 2017 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/products/books/amazing-animals-2018|title=Amazing Animals}}</ref>\n\nHis tricks have been documented on video on various media outlets, and he has been featured in articles by ''Huffington Post'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini The Bunny Plays Basketball Like A Pro|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/06/10/bini-the-bunny-plays-basketball-like-a-pro_n_3417391.html|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> AOL,<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini The Bunny Plays Basketball|url=http://www.aol.co.uk/video/bini-the-bunny-plays-basketball-517813168/|website=AOL UK|accessdate=15 February 2017}}</ref> ''USA Today'', ''Fox News'', and Sky News, among others. In 2016, Bini the Bunny was featured on LittleThings.com by Jessica Rothhaar<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini The Bunny Plays Basketball And Paints Works Of Art|url=https://www.littlethings.com/bini-the-bunny-paints/|website=Little Things|accessdate=1 November 2016}}</ref> and on German TV Network RTL Germany on the variety show ''Best Of'' .\nIn July 2017, Bini the Bunny and Shai Lighter were featured on the UK Channel E4 [[Rude Tube]] show, Season 11, Episode 9<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini on UK Channel E4 - Rude Tube|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZgcJdINRI1Y|website=Youtube}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Bini was invited to the Red Carpet Premiere for the Peter Rabbit movie as a \"celebrity rabbit\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/james-corden-peter-rabbit-premiere-1202686674|title=Red Carpet|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n\nOn September 27, 2018, Bini the Bunny's first short-feature film was released to the world, titled '''Rabbit Home Alone''' which features Shai Lighter, and an array of actors as well as Bin<ref>{{Citation|last=Bini the Bunny|title=Rabbit Home Alone (full version) - Home Alone Parody|date=2018-09-27|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0j8Gt5JQPKc|access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref> i.  The movie is a parody of 1990 feature film [[Home Alone]].\n\nIn 2019, Bini was featured in [[National Geographic]]'s book - Weird But True! USA. The book describes 300 facts about the United States, and Bini's fact is about a rabbit in LA that can slam dunk.\n\nIn June of 2019, Bini the Bunny and his owner Shai Lighter were interviewed on Australia's [[The Morning Show (TV program)|The Morning Show]] on Channel 7. \n\n== Hoppy Brush - Bini's puzzle game app ==\nIn February 2020, Shai Lighter released a mobile game based on Bini the Bunny's life.\nThe game is called Hoppy Brush, where players match colors to create paintings. In the game, Bini sells these paintings to help him rescue his mother.\nAll profits from the game go to the real life Bini and Shai Lighter.\n\n== Awards ==\n\nBini the Bunny was recognized and awarded a record by [[Guinness World Records]] for most slam dunks by a rabbit in 60 seconds.  Bini broke the record in October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title= The 2018 Guinness Book of World Records, in pictures|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/07/2018-guinness-book-world-records-pictures/bini-bunny-has-record-slam-dunks-rabbit/}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the Facebook page for Bini the Bunny was recognized as \"official\" by Facebook. Bini has more than 200,000 Facebook fans.<ref>{{cite web|title=Facebook Bini the Bunny|url=https://www.facebook.com/binithebunny/|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, YouTube awarded Bini and Shai the Silver Creator Award for reaching and passing 100,000 subscribers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini Silver Award|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VJJsTPvIFxU|website=Youtube}}</ref>\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite web | title=Conhe\u00e7a Bini the Bunny: o coelhinho pintor e jogador de basquete | website=[[Correio Braziliense]] | date=August 22, 2016 | url=http://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/app/noticia/mundo/2016/08/22/interna_mundo,545377/conheca-bini-the-bunny-o-coelhinho-pintor-e-jogador-de-basquete.shtml | language=pt | ref=harv | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}\n* {{cite web | title=Rencontre avec Bini, le lapinou le plus g\u00e9nial de toute la plan\u00e8te! | website=Le Tribunal Du Net | date=August 25, 2016 | url=http://www.letribunaldunet.fr/animaux/bini-le-lapin-qui-sait-tout-faire.html | language=fr | ref={{sfnref | Le Tribunal Du Net | 2016}} | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}\n* {{cite web | last=Smart | first=Tasha | title=Bini the Bunny combs his owner's hair using a comb in his mouth | website=Capital Bay News | date=June 20, 2016 | url=http://www.capitalbay.news/female/1049991-bini-the-bunny-combs-his-owner-s-hair-using-a-comb-in-his-mouth.html | ref=harv | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}\n* {{cite web | title=Slam-dunking bunny makes it into record book | website=Sky News | date=September 7, 2017 | url=http://news.sky.com/video/slam-dunking-bunny-makes-it-into-record-book-11024075 | accessdate=September 10, 2017}}\n* {{cite web | title=Bini the slam-dunking bunny is better than you at basketball | website=Independent IE | date=September 7, 2017 | url=http://www.independent.ie/world-news/and-finally/bini-the-slamdunking-bunny-is-better-than-you-at-basketball-36109714.html | accessdate=September 10, 2017}}\n* {{cite web | title=The 2018 Guinness Book of World Records, in pictures | website=The Telegraph | date=September 7, 2017 | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/07/2018-guinness-book-world-records-pictures/bini-bunny-has-record-slam-dunks-rabbit | accessdate=September 10, 2017}}\n\n[[Category:Individual rabbits]]\n[[Category:2012 animal births]]\n[[Category:Animals on the Internet]]\n[[Category:Male mammals]]\n[[Category:Visual arts by animals]]\n[[Category:World record holders]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreliable sources|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox animal\n| name                    = Bini the Bunny\n| image                   =Bini and his art.jpg\n| image_upright           = \n| caption                 = Bini and some of his paintings.\n| species                 = ''[[Domestic Rabbit]]''\n| breed                   = [[Holland Lop]]\n| gender                  = Male\n| birth_date              = {{Birth date and age|2012|3|21|mf=yes}}\n| occupation              = \n| employer                = \n| role                    = \n| years_active            = 2012\u2013present\n| known                   = [[Internet Celebrity]]\n| tricks                  = Basketball, Painting, Hair Styling\n| awards                  = Guinness World Record\n| title                   = \n| term                    = \n| predecessor             = \n| successor               = \n| owner                   = Shai Lighter\n| residence               = Los Angeles, California U.S. \n| parents                 = Unknown\n| children                = \n| weight                  = 5 lbs\n| height                  = \n| appearance              = \n| namedafter              = \n| website                 = {{url|http://www.facebook.com/Binithebunny}}\n}}\n'''Bini the Bunny''' is a rabbit, known for a series of videos posted on the internet.<ref>{{cite web | title=Bini, basketball's baddest bunny | website=[[Ynet]] | date=December 31, 1999 | url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4485656,00.html | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}</ref> Bini is a 8-year-old male [[Holland Lop]] rabbit, referred to by the media and fans as the only rabbit in the world who can paint,<ref>{{cite web|title=Talented Little Bunny Creates Beautiful Works Of Art, All On His Own!|url=http://www.jumblejoy.com/artist-bunny|website=Jumble Joy|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> play basketball,<ref>{{cite web | last=Schwartz | first=Nick | title=Here's a bunny that can dunk a basketball | publisher=[[CNN]] | date=June 11, 2013 | url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2013/06/heres-a-bunny-that-can-dunk-a-basketball | accessdate=February 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Meet Bini, The Basketball-Dunking Bunny|url=http://www.thepostgame.com/blog/animal-house/201306/meet-bini-basketball-dunking-bunny|website=The Post Game|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> and comb and style hair. \nAs of 2017, Bini and his owner, Shai (Asor) Lighter are [[Guinness World Records|Guinness Book of World Record]] holders for the most slam dunks by a rabbit in one minute.  \nBini's most popular video with over 20 million views was created in 2016, titled \"When Your Bunny is Addicted to Arcade Games\".<ref>{{cite web|title=When your bunny is addicted to arcade games...|url=https://www.facebook.com/binithebunny/videos/705862269561334/|website=Facebook.com|publisher=Bini the Bunny}}</ref> Bini's YouTube channel has more than 180,000 subscribers and his Facebook page has over 250,000 fans.\n\n== Background ==\nBini has starred in more than 60 videos where his talents and intelligence are exemplified. He first became recognizable through his 2013 YouTube video \"Funny bunny plays basketball -Bini the bunny\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Funny bunny plays basketball -Bini the bunny|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r7mC6Q-PSAw|website=Youtube|accessdate=10 September 2017}}</ref> In 2016, Bini and his owner Shai moved from Israel to Los Angeles, California.\n\nBini the Bunny's tricks include playing basketball, painting<ref>{{cite web|title=Monday blues? This PAINTING RABBIT will cheer you right up|url=http://www.shemazing.net/tag/bini-the-bunny/|website=Shemazing.net|accessdate=15 February 2017}}</ref> with acrylic paints on canvas, combing and brushing humans' hair, jumping, dancing and spinning on command.\n\n== Media appearances ==\n\nBini the Bunny and Shai Lighter appeared on [[The Gong Show]] on ABC on July 26, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Gong Show|url=https://abc.go.com/shows/the-gong-show/episode-guide/season-02/6-alyson-hannigan-will-arnett-lil-rel-howery#recap|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref> The Gong Show starring [[Mike Myers]], and featured celebrity judges: Will Arnett, [[Alyson Hannigan]], and Lil Rel Howery\n\nBini was featured on the cover of Guinness World Records: Amazing Animals released in September 2017 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/products/books/amazing-animals-2018|title=Amazing Animals}}</ref>\n\nHis tricks have been documented on video on various media outlets, and he has been featured in articles by ''Huffington Post'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini The Bunny Plays Basketball Like A Pro|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/06/10/bini-the-bunny-plays-basketball-like-a-pro_n_3417391.html|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> AOL,<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini The Bunny Plays Basketball|url=http://www.aol.co.uk/video/bini-the-bunny-plays-basketball-517813168/|website=AOL UK|accessdate=15 February 2017}}</ref> ''USA Today'', ''Fox News'', and Sky News, among others. In 2016, Bini the Bunny was featured on LittleThings.com by Jessica Rothhaar<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini The Bunny Plays Basketball And Paints Works Of Art|url=https://www.littlethings.com/bini-the-bunny-paints/|website=Little Things|accessdate=1 November 2016}}</ref> and on German TV Network RTL Germany on the variety show ''Best Of'' .\nIn July 2017, Bini the Bunny and Shai Lighter were featured on the UK Channel E4 [[Rude Tube]] show, Season 11, Episode 9<ref>{{cite web|title=Bini on UK Channel E4 - Rude Tube|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZgcJdINRI1Y|website=Youtube}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Bini was invited to the Red Carpet Premiere for the Peter Rabbit movie as a \"celebrity rabbit\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/james-corden-peter-rabbit-premiere-1202686674|title=Red Carpet|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n\nOn September 27, 2018, Bini the Bunny's first short-feature film was released to the world, titled '''Rabbit Home Alone''' which features Shai Lighter, and an array of actors as well as Bin<ref>{{Citation|last=Bini the Bunny|title=Rabbit Home Alone (full version) - Home Alone Parody|date=2018-09-27|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0j8Gt5JQPKc|access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref> i.  The movie is a parody of 1990 feature film [[Home Alone]].\n\nIn 2019, Bini was featured in [[National Geographic]]'s book - Weird But True! USA. The book describes 300 facts about the United States, and Bini's fact is about a rabbit in LA that can slam dunk.\n\nIn June of 2019, Bini the Bunny and his owner Shai Lighter were interviewed on Australia's [[The Morning Show (TV program)|The Morning Show]] on Channel 7. \n\n== Hoppy Brush - Bini's puzzle game app ==\nIn February 2020, Shai Lighter released a mobile game based on Bini the Bunny's life.\nThe game is called Hoppy Brush, where players match colors to create paintings. In the game, Bini sells these paintings to help him rescue his mother.\nAll profits from the game go to the real life Bini and Shai Lighter.\n\n== Awards ==\n\nBini the Bunny was recognized and awarded a record by [[Guinness World Records]] for most slam dunks by a rabbit in 60 seconds.  Bini broke the record in October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title= The 2018 Guinness Book of World Records, in pictures|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/07/2018-guinness-book-world-records-pictures/bini-bunny-has-record-slam-dunks-rabbit/}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the Facebook page for Bini the Bunny was recognized as \"official\" by